The White House Budget Director, Peter R. Orszag, will be delivering remarks on the economy at the Council on Foreign Relations' C. Peter McColough Series on International Economics in New York. He will discuss the country's progress in economic recovery, efforts to make critical investments, restore fiscal discipline, and establish a foundation for growth in the economy. The event is open to accredited journalists only, and media logistics and credentialing are being handled by the Council on Foreign Relations. The event will take place on Wednesday, July 22, 2009, at The Harold Pratt House in New York. RSVP is required by 9:00 a.m. on July 22, 2009, and press contact information is provided for further inquiries.